  "description": [
    "TWO THE MAUI NEWS FRIDAY APRIL 11 1919 Rice Fathers Anti Bolsheviki Measure Bill In Senate Prescribes Severe Pen No Intention Now To Retain Commer Navy Soon To Turn Back Radio System alties For Criminal Syndicalism Defined As Doctrine Advocating Sa botage To Accomplish Ends Special to Maul News HONOLflAT April 9 Action to ward heading off anything like a Bol shevik movement in the territory was taken in the legislature recently when Senator Harold V Rice introduced a bill defining criminal syndicalism and prescribing heavy penalties for every phase of it The bill which follows iilonu the lines of the law enacted in California recently Is as follows Section 1 Criminal syndicalism is hereby defined to be the doctrine which advocates crime sabotage vio lence or other unlawful methods of terrorism as a means of accomplish ing industrial or political ends Sec 2 Any person who 1 By word of mouth or writing ad vocates or teaches the duty neces sity or propriety of crime sabotage violence of other unlawful methods of terrorism as a means of accomplish ing industrial or political ends or 2 Prints publishes edits Issues or knowingly circulates sells dis tributes or publicly displays any"
